  "texts": [
    "Neglecting these critical measurement properties could lead to serious ethical issues, potentially resulting in erroneous conclusions about students' abilities, which could unfairly influence their educational paths.",
    "For example, in low-stakes assessments, students might not benefit if they are not properly designed to identify their misconceptions and provide valuable feedback about their learning progress.",
    "Therefore, test developers must integrate rigorous pre-testing and validation protocols within the AIG framework.",
    "Encouragingly, this gap has been swiftly addressed as more and more researchers have realized the importance of evaluating measurement properties after item generation in AIG (e.g., Sauberli & Clematide, 2024).We advocate that AIG research adopt a human-in-the-loop framework-a collaborative approach to integrate human expertise into AI-based decision-making.",
    "Relying solely on computer-generated items raises ethical concerns, given that assessments play a fundamental role in evaluating students' learning outcomes and monitoring the performance of larger entities such as schools and education systems (Gierl et al., 2022)."
  ],
